en_129918_0	A stock of heroin, weighing 101 kilos, was taken into custody in the South Sea, while it was on route to Sri Lanka.
en_129918_1	The stock was seized during a joint operation carried out by the Sri Lanka Navy and Police Narcotics Bureau.
en_129918_2	Fourteen people, including ten Iranians and a Pakistani national, were arrested in connection with the incident.
en_129918_3	Police say that the racket was carried out by Sri Lankans with the collaboration of Pakistan and Afganistan nationals.
en_129918_4	Sri Lanka Navy said that the illegal drugs are transported to Colombo through the Southern Expressway.
